article.description: — Jayson Petty's 21 points helped UMKC defeat South Dakota 81-57 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Petty scores 21 to lead Kansas City over South Dakota 81-57
article.linkText: Petty scores 21 to lead Kansas City over South Dakota 81-57
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- — Jayson Petty's 21 points helped UMKC defeat South Dakota 81-57 on Saturday night. Petty also added five rebounds for the Kangaroos (9-13, 3-4 Summit League). Khristion Courseault was 4 of 8 shooting and 8 of 13 from the free throw line to add 17 points. Jamar Brown had 14 points and was 5 of 10 shooting, including 1 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line. The Coyotes (9-13, 2-5) were led by Lahat Thioune, who posted 20 points, nine rebounds and two steals. South Dakota also got 14 points from Kaleb Stewart. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
